Experiment 3: GitHub Repository Creation and Push

Step 1: Configure Git (one time)
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your_email@example.com"

Step 2: Create repository on GitHub
(Login to GitHub → New Repository → Name: git-lab-demo → Public → Create)

Step 3: Clone the GitHub repository
cd Desktop
git clone https://github.com/YourUsername/git-lab-demo.git
cd git-lab-demo

Step 4: Create a local file
notepad main.py

(Type the following content in main.py)
print("This file is from local machine")

Save and close the file.

Step 5: Add and commit the file
git add main.py
git commit -m "Add main.py file"

Step 6: Push local code to GitHub
git push -u origin main

Step 7: Modify file on GitHub (online)
(Edit README.md and add: Updated via GitHub)

Step 8: Pull changes from GitHub
git pull origin main

Step 9: Verify updates
git status
git log
